snippet: Gov. Jay Nixon vetoed a bill that called on the state to prosecute federal officials who try to enforce federal gun laws in Missouri and prohibit publication of gun owners’ names.
abstract: Missouri Gov Jay Nixon vetoes bill that would have called on the state to prosecute federal officials who try to enforce federal gun laws in state and prohibit publication of the names of people owning guns.
lead_paragraph: Gov. Jay Nixon vetoed a bill that called on the state to prosecute federal officials who try to enforce federal gun laws in Missouri and prohibit publication of gun owners’ names.
